Preheat oven to 300 degrees F. Spray bottom of 9-inch springform pan with non-stick cooking spray. Combine graham cracker crumbs and sugar; sprinkle evenly on bottom of pan. In large bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy. Mix in cocoa and flour. Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Pour into prepared pan. Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until center is set. Cool. Chill. Garnish as desired. Store leftovers covered in refrigerator.